metadata.name: Distribution for Ukraine
metadata.description:
This is a fundraising piece to support victims of the Ukraine invasion.

100% of proceedings will go directly to a smart contract that will direct the funds to a list of NGOs operating in Ukraine, as suggested by The Giving Block (@TheGivingBlock). The contract has been set up as an initiative proposed by @Veqtor (@VersumOfficial) and @Ciphrd (@fx_hash_).

You can also send donations directly in Tezos to the smart contract (**only tezos**, not tokens). The smart contract address is:
KT1DWnLiUkNtAQDErXxudFEH63JC6mqg3HEx

The source code for the contract is here:
https://github.com/ciphrd/public-contracts/blob/master/donations_ukraine.py

The list of NGOs is here:
https://twitter.com/TheGivingBlock/status/1496910223034155008

The program generates blurring and shifting of various distributions of the input image pixels changed with the alternator depend on numbers given by the hash. Random color of the white square input image stroke is the source of all color values.  Polydiagonal multiplier: the shape of the fractal {0, 1, 2, 4, …, 256}
Segmentation: {on, off}
Subdivision movement: {up, stable, down} Angle: {-45°, 0°, 45°} Side: {left, right} Direction: {left, right} Alternator module: every which value of the input image tones is changed to 0 {2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7}
Gear: the number of extra blur and alternator per frame {1, 2, 3}  

Thanks for collecting
Proembrion 03-04-2022

metadata.name: The Seventh Circle
metadata.description:
The Seventh Circle

"Now I would have you know: the other time
that I descended into lower Hell,
this mass of boulders had not yet collapsed."


- The canvas is split into between 64 and 256 areas. Each area is separated from its neighbours by a border of between 1.5% and 4.5% of the canvas.

- Each area is further subdivided into between 64 and 100 smaller squares. These are separated by a proportionally-smaller border.

- A time-based function affects the hue of each square, mapping the sin and cosine of each squares position, offset by an amount determined from the initial hash. Over time, the colour of the squares will change, dependent on further initial values.

- Occasionally, sections of each grid will break away, rendering at an angle to the main piece. Within this, individual squares may be rotated slightly.

- The overlaid texture may be dark or bright, horizontally or vertically. The texture size may vary according to the initial conditions.


Most importantly, with the fullness of time, all pieces have a chance of returning to wholeness; they are all a part of a cycle of life, that each one may know its place.

Almost anything can be forgiven.

metadata.name: spaceplant
metadata.description:
Natural processes are computational at their very core, and like atoms, gravity, electricity, the sun, the moon, and the big bang, computation tells part of our cosmological story.

The "spaceplant" series expresses this "computational beauty of nature" (a phrase borrowed from Gary William Flake's book of that title) through a lo-fi simulated garden. This garden has been grown by collecting, curating and nurturing algorithmic specimens that inhabit a space both cellular and planetary. A symphony of particle forces orchestrates the form and interaction of the simulation, tuned to cosmological constants by the artist.

49 kB of compiled JavaScript. Code written 100% from scratch with no dependencies. Mouse interactive.

Dutch auction at 18:00 UTC, Mar 4 2020, starting at 80 tez and going down to 15 tez.

metadata.name: Growth One
metadata.description:
Growth One

by Daeinc
March 2022
  
A growth simulation of a virtual micro organism that follows simple rules. The organism starts with a few seed nodes, and it grows when the seed nodes and search nodes accept each other when they meet certain conditions. The organism loosely resembles structures found in nature such as coral reef or fungus. Do we embrace the beauty of its emerging structure or reject it because of pathogenic associations?  
  
Instructions:
  - The simulation may take some time to finish.
  - press [spacebar] - start/stop breathing animation
  - press [b] - alternative grey backgrounds
  - press [s] - export high resolution PNG image
  - press [p] - play or pause the entire animation
  - real time growth mode - You can simulate the growth in real-time by adding "realtime" parameter to the end of the URL in live view. (ex. https://ipfs.io/.../?fxhash=...&realtime)
  
License
CC-BY-NC 4.0
p5js library was used for html5 canvas codes. No modification other than bundling was made to the library. g.js library was referenced for vector graphics. canvas-sketch was used to build/bundle the project. Please refer to the included LICENSE.md for license information.

metadata.name: Ame-onna
metadata.description:
Morning cloud...evening rain.

On rainy days and nights, they summon rain wherever they go, and are blamed for kidnapping and spiriting away children.

Ame-onna go back to the ancient folk religions of Japan and China. The rains were said to be brought by benevolent gods and goddesses who lived as clouds by morning and as rain by night, forever traveling between heaven and earth. Legend has it that some of these rain-bringing goddesses became corrupted and devolved into evil yōkai. They abandoned their divinity to live among mortals and prey upon them.

metadata.name: TOASTY
metadata.description:
I'm feeling hungry, maybe it's time for a Toasty...

Find which of those randomized toasts is better for you and try to find the perfect recipes!
Salted or sweet, each combination will be perfect! Or will you throw up on sight? 

The randomized features include:
• colorful background
• personalized hashtag
• homemade bread 
• base ingredient
• additional ingredient
• topping

Please note that all our toasts are made with the freshest ingredients and homemade bread.
There are no traits rarer than others, but it's very difficult to find one that's edible!
A "chef guide" with 5 perfect combinations will be posted on Twitter (@stefj_art)

This project was made with PureSpider FXHASH PFP Token generator, a boilerplate to automate and ease the creation of profile picture projects on fxhash.

metadata.name: ACCUMULATOR
metadata.description:
A fully procedural and real-time simulated circuit, with 8 oscillating input signals and an output screen!

Each chip stores the incoming signals energy and propagates it to all its connected counterparts.

The animation on the screen is the result of all this accumulated signals.

Features:
 - 4 screen colors
 - 15 screen resolutions (sides can be 4, 8, 16, 32 or 64 pixels)
 - 42% chance for the circuit to be symmetrical on the X-axis
 - 24% chance for Y-axis symmetry only if already X-symmetrical
 - 13.37% chance for a shiny foil overlay
 - different "chipset manufacturer codes" based on PCB and chips color combinations

[Realized in vanilla JS with love and madness]
(everything is procedurally generated)

metadata.name: Not A World
metadata.description:
Meet here a collection of tiny procedural worlds generated with a random noise. Each planet is different, with random matching colors, based on the height of the different vertices. 
 There are 3 levels of rarity : Common, Rare, Legendary.

This is a ThreeJS experience, with custom shaders, post-processing, many random parameters, and a lot of love. Everything is handled by the GPU to increase performances and give you a better mint.

There are 365 iterations, based on the revolution period of the Earth, but remember, this is not a world. The price will give you a hint.

metadata.name: Genome hash Analysis
metadata.description:
+ VisualArt based on your unique fxhash as an output.

Every mint gets an analysis of its genome, using as seed the alphanumeric string that makes up its unique hash.



Features

Random Number:
It is the variable corresponding to fxrand()

NFT-HashSeed: 
All the numbers that make up the alphanumeric hash are added, to generate the seed from those unique values.

Color Palette Group:
There are 10 groups corresponding to the color palette, which add up to a total of 100 possible combinations.



* Rare variations are created for 50% of the editions.

* Your unique hash is translated into a visual genome scan.

metadata.name: Digital Images for Analog Eyes
metadata.description:
An attempt at capturing a uniquely digital aesthetic in code-generated images.
Alternatively this is just experimentation with color, noise and the modulo operator.

Details may vary per device, aspect ratio and window size

Generative images by @0x3739
Visuals are code-generated
library: twgljs - A Tiny WebGL helper Library
License: CC-BY-NC-SA 4.0

controls
'-' to zoom in.
'+' to zoom out.
'k' to decompose/pixelize the image.
Can take up to 10 decomposing steps before the effect is visible.
'8' or 'arrow_up' to move up in the image.
'5' or 'arrow_down' to move down in the image.
'6' or 'arrow_right' to move right in the image.
'4' or 'arrow_left' to move left in the image.
'1,f,w,a' to change the aspect ratio.
's' to save an image of the canvas.
'h' to increase the quality modifier (maximum is 5).
'l' to decrease the quality modifier (minimum is 1).
The quality modifier is a modifier on the width and height of the canvas.
Changing the modifier can affect the look of the image due to subpixel artifacts.
Use the modifier to save higher resolution images.

metadata.description:
ANGRY NOISE Compositions. Live WebGL shader. By Piter Pasma (https://piterpasma.nl).

Keyboard controls:
a/b/c/d/e resolution multiplier. 
1/2/3/4/5 set tiling to NxN, press repeatedly to see all tiles.
Save and combine to get a gigantic poster sized image.

For more information, read the code.

metadata.name: Modular Permutation
metadata.description:
The permutation of sounds and colors tries to understand the natural order of numbers and their forms represented in nature, silence is where that number meets infinity, noise is the movement of air, silence flows like this the chaos of numbers, creating the abstract . this abstract simulation is part of a cultural context and a digital effervescence, where computers are no longer tools and become co-authors in the random factor that simulates chaos in this modular composition, both in image and in sound.

by Marcelo Moura · Brazil, 2022 | GTK:javascript/hydra'ojack Music: vcvrack

metadata.name: Weavemaker Mega
metadata.description:
Multiple full size weaves formulated by between 2 to 5 uniquely located walkers over 1250 frames.
Satisfying to watch the reveal, some palettes take a little longer than others to start to reveal.
Rarity includes:
- One of twenty palettes each with 5% rarity, although some may turn out rarer than others.
- Number of Walkers (2 to 5)
- Location of each Walker

Made by P1xelboy :
@p1x3lboy Mar 2022

metadata.name: Heat Deserts🏜️
metadata.description:
You now have possession of a VERY HOT Desert! or cold, exactly. It has features that can change the climate of your desert.
Completely procedural to have a different experience every time you enter.

Exclusive features:
HUG ❤️🌵
STONEHENGE 💎
CLIMATE 🌎
DUST STORM 🏜️🌪
DAY/NIGHT ☀️🌙

⚠️Have a better experience by pressing "Open"

Quick Guide (GOD MODE - KEYBOARD "G" ):
Right mouse button - Navigate.
Left mouse button - Move items / Spawn HUG🌵.
Scroll button pressed + move mouse - Rotate view
Scroll button pressed over item - Rotate item.

Quick Guide (CREATURE MODE - KEYBOARD "C" ):
W,A,S,D - Navigate.
Move mouse - Rotate view
Spacebar - Jump.
Shift - Run

Enjoy!

metadata.name: NotSoDumbAss
metadata.description:
Donkeys have a well-deserved reputation for obstinacy, which has been attributed to a far stronger sense of self-preservation than other animals. It is much more difficult to compel or frighten a donkey into performing anything it thinks to be harmful for whatever reason, likely due to a stronger prey drive and a lesser bond with people.

NotSoDumbAss is a set of 30 donkey NFTs with a layer of rectangular and circular pixels in a variety of colours overlaid on top.

metadata.name: Psychedelic Bounce
metadata.description:
Psychedelic Bounce re-imagines one of the first graphical video games [Pong] through the lens of a psychedelic experience - complete with persistent tracers, vivid saturated colors and monochromatics, random coloring and banding, changing puck shape with fixed and modulating puck sizes, and drawing with transparency. Psychedelic Bounce pauses drawing every 33 bounces and switches to a super trippy quad symmetry output. When the display is put in fullscreen, the default 1:1 aspect ratio is stretched to fill the screen.

All features can be manipulated interactively using the keyboard.
- Space key or mouse click starts/stops puck drawing
(drawing starts with quad symmetry off: enable with 'q' key)
(stopping drawing turns quad symmetry on: disable with 'q' key)
- 'q' or 'Q' - quad symmetry (on/off)
- 'r' or 'R' - rotate quad symmetry by 90 degrees
- 'p' or 'P' - auto pausing function (on/off)
(pausing turns quad symmetry off: enable with 'q' key)
- 'g' or 'G' - puck shape (square/circle/both)
- 'x' or 'X' - monochrome/full color
(background remain the initial monochrome or full color)
- 'c' or 'C' - select random puck color
- 'a' or 'A' - random color draw every other bounce (on/off)
- 'e' or 'E' - random color on every puck draw
(only works with random color draw every other bounce on)
- 'b' or 'B' - color banding (on/off)
(banding color is complementary color of the puck color)
- 'm' or 'M' - puck modulation (on/off)
- 't' or 'T' - transparency (on/off)
- '1' - slowest (1 fps) puck drawing
- '2' - slower (10 fps) puck drawing
- '3' - faster (30 fps) puck drawing
(fps rate may not be accurate if quad symmetry enabled)
- 's' - save 4000 x 4000 pixel png image with border
- [shift]'S' - save 4000 x 4000 pixel png image without border
(fullscreen saved images are screen dimensions X 2)
- 'n' or 'N' - re-initializes the gentk

Rarity features are written to the console at loading and whenever changed interactively.

March 2022
coded by StreamDreamz (a.k.a. Freakiebeat)
coded with - html, css, javascript, p5.js

License: NFT License 2.0

metadata.name: Chaos and Order
metadata.description:
Chaos and Order is a series of generative art created by mashing together many lines.

The intention in creating these works was to express a combination of chaos and order.

Chaos and Order is created by p5js.Each piece is 640 x 640.

Press 's' in live view to save the current image.

For each token, colors, noiseSeed, numbers of particles, lifes of particles, are generated, resulting in unique generative patterns for each minted item.

The minting price is low but the number of minting is large, so that everyone can explore more styles.
